import{_ as t,c as a,b as o,o as r}from"./chunks/framework.Bh4f_7Kc.js";const f=JSON.parse('{"title":"","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[],"relativePath":"guide/Eisenhower.md","filePath":"guide/Eisenhower.md"}'),i={name:"guide/Eisenhower.md"};function n(s,e,h,p,d,l){return r(),a("div",null,e[0]||(e[0]=[o("<p>Remember well: prudence and cowardice are not synonymous, just as bravery is not the same as recklessness!</p><p>---002---</p><p>No matter who you are, when you accept the cheers earned with the blood of your subordinates and the sacrifice of your friends, you must always remember to be humble.</p><p>---003---</p><p>Accomplishment is the journey, not the destination.</p><p>---004---</p><p>In my family, caring about others is a matter of course. My parents taught us from a young age that a person should be ambitious but not arrogant, and that self-reliance is the basic principle of life.</p><p>---005---</p><p>&quot;The atomic bomb&#39;s greatest power is when it&#39;s on the launch pad, not when it&#39;s launched.</p><p>---006---</p><p>Science is a bit like the air you breathe—it&#39;s everywhere.</p><p>---007---</p><p>One dollar spent on foreign propaganda is equal to five dollars spent on national defense.</p><p>---008---</p><p>Our basic belief is that the state exists for the benefit of the people, not the people for the benefit of the state.</p><p>---009---</p><p>There is no tragedy in life，like the death of a child, things never get back to the way they were.——President Dwight Eisenhower</p><p>The saddest thing in life is the death of a child. Everything is changed beyond recognition and can never be restored to its original state.</p><p>---010---</p><p>I cannot tolerate those extreme rightists who call everyone who disagrees with them red, and I cannot tolerate those extreme leftists who shout that the rest of us are cruel money-grubbers.</p><p>---011---</p><p>The soldiers of Free France made an indescribable contribution to the Normandy Landing.</p><p>At the time of the landings, the French Resistance had a strength equivalent to 10-15 divisions.</p><p>---012---</p><p>The Second World War was not started by the people of the United States and its allies. They were not foolish warmongers. Those who survived the war and served their country still remember clearly that they fought on the battlefield to avoid being ravaged by the enemy. For this purpose, countless heroes sacrificed their lives for the country, and they left a deep mark in our hearts.</p><p>---013---</p><p>Our landings in the Cherbourg-Havre area have not gained a satisfactory foothold, and I have ordered the troops to withdraw. My decision to attack at this time and place was based on the best information available. Our military, air force and navy have performed their duties bravely and faithfully. If there is any blame for this attack, or any fault in this attack, it is my personal responsibility.</p>",27)]))}const u=t(i,[["render",n]]);export{f as __pageData,u as default};
